submitScore

public void submitScore(float score,
                        java.lang.String data,
                        SwarmLeaderboard.SubmitScoreCB cb)
Submit a score to the Leaderboard.

Parameters:
score - The score to be submitted.
data - A String that is included with the score submission. If not needed, an empty string is an acceptable value.
cb - The callback that returns after an attempt to submit the score. If the submission is successful the callback returns the user's Leaderboard rank (in the form of an int) and displays a Swarm notification to the user which contains the user's name, user's rank, and user's score. If the submission fails, then the callback returns -1.

                            java.lang.String scope,
                            SwarmLeaderboard.GotScoresCB cb)
Get a specified page of scores for the Leaderboard. Page 0 contains the top scores for the Leaderboard.

Parameters:
pageNum - The Leaderboard page number requested.
dateRange - The date range requested, one of SwarmLeaderboard.LEADERBOARD_DATE_XXXXXX.
scope - The scope of the scores requested, one of LEADERBOARD_SCOPE_XXXXX.
cb - The callback returns the Leaderboard page number and Leaderboard ID on success, and returns -1 on failure.
